    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/60.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The minister for foreign affairs has informed him that authorization to conclude
                    a convention for the submission of the boundary question to arbitration was sent
                    to the Dominican minister at Washington by last mail. He also stated that his
                    Government does not confine itself to arbitration by The Hague Tribunal and will
                    accept such other form of arbitration as may be decided upon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
